Access to an electronic device with video and microphone capabilities
The ability to conduct the telehealth visit in a private location

Primary Care is your first stop for most health questions and concerns. We specialize in college health. Our primary care professionals address physical and emotional issues, acute and chronic conditions, and prevention and health maintenance.
Colds, flus, fevers, sore throats   Rashes, skin issues   Infections   Constipation   Indigestion   Post-travel infections
Asthma   Hypertension   Type 2 diabetes   Acne, including Accutane prescribing   Joint pains, arthritis   Irritable bowel, chronic constipation/diarrhea
Preventive and well-person examinations, women's health and immigration exams, or to complete a form (sports, travel or study abroad).
We provide contraception, pregnancy testing, HIV testing, and sexually transmitted infection (STI) testing and treatment.
You can receive routine vaccinations. For travel vaccines, visit our Travel Clinic.
We perform mole removals, skin biopsies, ingrown toenail removal and joint injections.
We are not offering allergy injections at this time.
Call our Nurse Line at 612-625-7900 if you do not know what type of clinic you need. Calls answered 24/7.
How much will my visit cost?
It depends on your health insurance and whether you pay the Student Services Fee.

A co-payment at the time of your visit may apply. Any remaining costs for your care may be billed to you at a later time. Amounts vary by insurance plan. Consult your insurance card, or contact your health insurance provider for details.
With some exceptions, students who pay the Student Services Fee receive most services at Boynton at reduced cost. See details about the Student Services Fee.

MyU: For Students, Faculty, and Staff
Boynton Health requires patients to have health insurance coverage. We accept most insurance plans. Check with your health insurance provider to see if Boynton is in their provider network.
The University of Minnesota requires students to have health insurance. If you do not have insurance, you may be able to buy coverage from the Office of Student Health Benefits.
See details on the Office of Student Health Benefits website.

We take part in most UPlan health plans. UPlan members may be able to choose Boynton as their primary care clinic. Our Gopher Quick Clinic is open to most UPlan members with copayment, consult your insurance card for details.
Flu shots, health coaching and health screening are offered to UPlan members at no out-of-pocket cost. These benefits also earn Wellness Program points that can lower your UPlan premiums.
See details about the UPlan on the Office of Human Resources website.
If you have any questions about a bill, call our patient accounting department, 612-624-6985, or see billing information.
If you are a student who pays the Student Services Fee, the amount of your bill not covered by insurance will be paid for from the Student Services Feesome exceptions apply.
